  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nThe prater node is synced and there are 2 adjacent epoch transition calls (1 for `getBlockSlotState` and 1 for `runEpochTransition`), I suspect it's for the same epoch:\r\n<img width=\"1410\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-04-15 at 14 52 17\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/114833877-39adac00-9dfa-11eb-8d8b-d4eed35f182a.png\">\r\n\r\nAnd each epoch transition in the profiler is around 6s!\r\n\r\nWhat I guess:\r\n+ we receive a gossip block at start of an epoch and we have to do epoch transition to check block proposer https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/5ed277e2005484b0c8e77a2e2857d501d5b938c5/packages/lodestar/src/chain/validation/block.ts#L59\r\n+ then we do regular `runStateTransition()` which process slots (and epoch) and block inside `beacon-state-transition` module https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/5ed277e2005484b0c8e77a2e2857d501d5b938c5/packages/lodestar/src/chain/blocks/stateTransition.ts#L124\r\n\r\nIt happens 2 times in this profiler result \r\n[0415_prater_server_synced.cpuprofile.zip](https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/files/6316154/0415_prater_server_synced.cpuprofile.zip)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nWe should be able to do exactly 1 epoch transition leveraging our checkpoint cache there.\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\n\r\nSync prater until the node is synced and take profiler.",
